snippet.textDisplay:
Jamie Carragher is so unbearable to listen to when he's talking about Manchester United. This is a growing team. Forget the money that's been spent already - that isn't Ole's fault. He's improved the overall feel around the club and the players are showing better character in games. Still inconsistent? Yes. But nobody gets it 100% right first time around. Not even Pep with an already elite City team!

It's down to the board to go out and get players who will continue having that same fighting spirit. The signings over the summer are great examples of that. Build a strong base (which is starting to grow), then start going out and buying stars who can thrive with a great support.

snippet.textDisplay: Everyone needs to step back and get a little perspective. Fred and Rashford have improved drastically. McTominay, Williams and Greenwood have come in and looked promising, as have the three summer signings. Yes, we were well beat by a much better Liverpool side (who've had years together under the same manager) but we were missing three of our best players. We were unfortunate not to get Haaland (we're better off without Raiola players), but we'll more than likely get Fernandes in this window. We sign Maddison/Grealish, a new CB and striker in the summer and we'll look a lot more impressive come next season. Solskjaer doesn't want a quick fix and players who don't want to be here (Pogba, Sanchez, Lukaku, Di Maria, etc). He wants young, hungry talent that he can shape into a great team, just like Klopp did at Liverpool (7th in first season). Have faith and give the man a chance.

snippet.textDisplay:
am a Liverpool fan, and I may be later turn out to be wrong, but from day 1, I believe Ole is wrong appointment. he only won in Norway league, and got Cardiff relegated. to fix the mess at United he was coming to was too much.

to compare him (and ask him to be given same time) as Jurgen Klopp, is a bit far off. Klopp got mainz promoted, got Dortmund to UCL final. Ole got Cardiff relegated.

Roy has nostalgia, seeing Ole played. he is not objective. Ole is a legendary player, but not there yet as manager to handle a big club like Man United.

give him as much time as you like, United. your rivals are very happy you guys are patient.
